e. Dado
   $$k=A e^{-\frac{(\Delta G+\lambda)^2}{4\lambda RT}},$$
   temos que
   $$k=2k_0$$
   o que implica em
   $$A e^{-\frac{(\Delta G+\lambda)^2}{4\lambda R(T+37)}}=2A e^{-\frac{(\Delta G+\lambda)^2}{4\lambda RT}}$$
   $$\implies \frac{-(\Delta G+\lambda)^2}{4\lambda R(T+37)}=\ln 2-\frac{(\Delta G+\lambda)^2}{4\lambda RT}$$
   $$\implies \frac{(\Delta G+\lambda)^2}{4\lambda R}\left(-\frac{1}{(T+37)}+\frac{1}{T}\right)=\ln 2$$
   $$\implies \frac{(\Delta G+\lambda)^2}{4\lambda R}\left(\frac{37}{T(T+37)}\right)=\ln 2$$
   $$\implies \frac{(\Delta G+\lambda)^2}{\lambda}=\underbrace{\frac{4RT(T+37)\ln 2}{37}}_{\psi}$$
   Por Bhaskara, temos
   $$\lambda = \frac{1}{2}(\pm\sqrt{\psi^2-4\Delta G \psi}-2\Delta G +\psi)$$
